<div id="review_2580268043" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2580268043" />
    <a title="Deborah Obida" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54790180-deborah-obida"><img alt="Deborah Obida" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1604679377p2/54790180.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2580268043?book_show_action=true">Apr 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Deborah Obida" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Deborah Obida" href="/user/show/54790180-deborah-obida">Deborah Obida</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11812977-best-served-cold">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54790180-deborah-obida?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2580268043" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3408319307253137520"><b>
  <i>You can weep over your misfortunes, or you can pick yourself up and make the best of things, shit though they may be.</i>
</b><br/><br/>This book is a spin-off of the Initial first law trilogy, its not neccessary to read that before this, but it will help in understanding some terms.<br/><br/>This is the best portrayal of morally ambiguous character I&apos;ve ever read, all negativity. They trust someone as much as they can throw them which is not much, and to them Mercy and Cowardice is the same, who thinks like that, crazy</span>
  <span id="freeText3408319307253137520" style="display:none"><b>
  <i>You can weep over your misfortunes, or you can pick yourself up and make the best of things, shit though they may be.</i>
</b><br /><br />This book is a spin-off of the Initial first law trilogy, its not neccessary to read that before this, but it will help in understanding some terms.<br /><br />This is the best portrayal of morally ambiguous character I've ever read, all negativity. They trust someone as much as they can throw them which is not much, and to them Mercy and Cowardice is the same, who thinks like that, crazy murderous people. Despite their many flaws I love the characters in this book. <br /><br /><b>
  <i>There was such a thing as too much truth, especially in the ears of powerful men.</i>
</b><br /><br />The sole aim of this book is revenge, nothing more. Monza one of the main characters will do anything to get revenge for things done to her. The ironic thing is she is not even a good person. <br /><br /><b>
  <i><br />When you have a half-mad plan you need men at least half-mad to see it through. <br />Sane ones might be tempted to look for a better idea.</i>
</b><br /><br /><u>World building and Writing</u><br />The book is set in Styria, not in the Union like the first three books. Just like that one, this book has amazing world building and great depictions. The writing isn't bad either, the book is written in third person multiple POV of the main characters.<br /><br /><u>Characters</u><br />Monzacarro Murcatto is the protagonist. She is nicer than she lets on. A former Captain General of The thousand sword, a mercenary group. She will never purposefully waste a life. She is a badass sword fighter and a tid bit manipulative. Despite her many flaws I love her dedication, if she sets her mind to something, nothing can change that. She wants to exact revenge on Duke Orso, the most powerful man in Styria so she gathers a team.<br /><br /><b>
  <i>“When you build your life around only one thing, love only one person, dream only one dream, you risk losing everything at a stroke."</i>
</b><br /><br />Shivers the Northerner from The last argument of kings is in Styria so she hires him. Shivers started off so well but then shit happened.<br /><br />Nicoma Cosca another reoccurring character, he was Monza's mentor before they splitted up years ago. Also a part of the team. He is also a mercenary.<br /><br />Morveer is a poisoner with his assistant Day. They all made the team that wants to out Orso and six other people.<br /><br />This book is just amazing. if you like Grimdark, you will definitely like this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3408319307253137520" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


