<div id="review_825200174" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/825200174" />
    <a title="Silvana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/666003-silvana"><img alt="Silvana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1606622144p2/666003.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/825200174?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Silvana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Silvana" href="/user/show/666003-silvana">Silvana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6659140-best-served-cold">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=fyeahfantasy">fyeahfantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=dark-matter">dark-matter</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=kindle-google">kindle-google</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=z-sff-2019-standalone-challenge">z-sff-2019-standalone-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=stand-alones">stand-alones</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=mine-mine-mine">mine-mine-mine</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=reading-with-friends">reading-with-friends</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=z-sff-2019-reading-challenge">z-sff-2019-reading-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=dick-lit">dick-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/666003-silvana?shelf=girl-power">girl-power</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer825200174" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14900157848075510832">First reread:<br/>I still think this is one of Abercrombie&apos;s best works. And Cosca, you stole every scene, you lovable scoundrel. <br/><br/>Original review: <br/>It&apos;s been a long time since I felt shell-shocked after reading a book. That would be A Storm of Swords in 2011, I guess. Best Served Cold is now in my top five list of best fantasy novels ever graced this earth. Don&apos;t ask me about the complete list since I haven&apos;t actually made it since before that last sentence. <br/><br/>Cosca. Dear old Cosca. I understand now why</span>
  <span id="freeText14900157848075510832" style="display:none">First reread:<br />I still think this is one of Abercrombie's best works. And Cosca, you stole every scene, you lovable scoundrel. <br /><br />Original review: <br />It's been a long time since I felt shell-shocked after reading a book. That would be A Storm of Swords in 2011, I guess. Best Served Cold is now in my top five list of best fantasy novels ever graced this earth. Don't ask me about the complete list since I haven't actually made it since before that last sentence. <br /><br />Cosca. Dear old Cosca. I understand now why some friends said he was cooler than Glokta. Well, I tend to agree with another friend who said both had their own qualities. Wit, sarcasm, resourcefulness, both never failed to entertain me as a reader. Even though Glokta was definitely not as vivacious as Cosca. I want to have a drink with Cosca, he'd make an excellent companion. <br /><br />Back to the book. I think BSC towers over the First Law trilogy. I guess I am not really a fan of the mythology and magic and whatnots in the trilogy. I am more drawn to the characters and plots. And the banter. Omg Joe Abercrombie can really write amusing banters or inner thoughts. Can't remember how many times I actually LOLed during reading. The plots and the twists. Some you can kinda guess, but still ended up surprised and entertained at the end. Fast-moving, jaw-opening, insomnia-inducing writing. Bravo. <br /><br />The characters. I was kinda disappointed that the ruthless scheming lying mass-murdering Serpent of Talins was actually a softie, but Monza still rocks my socks. Hey, you don't get many kickass female characters like her. Well, maybe Cara Mason from that awful Terry Goodkind series which name escapes my mind entirely (and maybe deliberately because it really, really sucks). Speaking of characters, as I said before, reading this book is like having a reunion. Some beloved (or not so beloved) characters from the trilogy made appearances, which is cool. Totally agree that one should not read this book before the trilogy. Spoilers galore. <br /><br />The best new character would be Friendly I guess. He was just so loyal, simple and committed. I know why Cosca liked him a lot. Dependable, that's what he was. His OCD when it comes to numbers was adorkable. <br /><br />Again I love that this book has no protagonists or antagonists. Only shades of grey. It's just a matter of POV. All did what they had to do. I want to know more about the Thousand Swords. They reminded me of Glen Cook's Black Company actually. Wonder who would win if both mercenary units meet. I need more mercenary stories!</span>
  <a data-text-id="14900157848075510832" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


